definition: to arrange/to settle/to complete/to carry through
to do/to manage/to handle/to go about/to run/to set up/to deal with

sentences.english: Have you got through with the check-in procedure?
sentences.chinese: 你是否已經辦妥住宿註冊手續？

sentences.english: Have you completed the following tasks before submission of this application?
sentences.chinese: 遞交此申請表前，你是否已辦妥下列事項？

sentences.english: You must check in the equipment after using .
sentences.chinese: 這些器材用後必須辦妥手續歸還。

sentences.english: Please return your stamped Discharge Notice to the Nurse Station.
sentences.chinese: 請您將辦妥並蓋章之出院通知單繳回護理站。

sentences.english: A deposit of eight pounds clinched the bargain.
Just put your name on the dotted line and we'll be set.
sentences.chinese: 就在虛線上簽字吧，這樣我們就辦妥了。

sentences.english: That done, he had betaken himself to Montfermeil.
sentences.chinese: 辦妥了這兩件事以後他便到了孟費郿。

sentences.english: Those who complete the application for suspension before each semester will be exempted from the tuition fee.
sentences.chinese: 學期開始上課前辦妥休學者，免繳學雜費。

sentences.english: On June 6, the ship completed the departure formalities and from the port of Cape Town.
sentences.chinese: 6月6日，該船辦妥相關離港手續並駛離開普敦港。

sentences.english: Your reservation is hereby confirmed. Thank you for your support.
sentences.chinese: 閣下留位已辦妥，謝謝支持。

sentences.english: Sir, we have finished our hotel check-in. Could you please give us the room keys?
sentences.chinese: 先生，我們已辦妥入住登記，請給房間鑰匙好嗎？

sentences.english: I have made all the reservations for my trip.
sentences.chinese: 我已辦妥旅行的全部預訂。

sentences.english: This done, he left the hotel and began to wander about the town.
sentences.chinese: 事情辦妥以後，他便出了旅館，向城裏走去。

sentences.english: We'll complete the formalities for your entry visa as soon as possible.
sentences.chinese: 我們會盡快辦妥您的入境簽證手續的。

sentences.english: Have you already made a reservation?
The procedure should be completed before final exams scheduled on the school calendar.
sentences.chinese: 休學手續應於校曆明訂之學期考試前辦妥。
